data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":352,"item_id":"msg_0a7b650210d820fc00693a1e281e888193be6ff304611ba4cb","output_index":4,"content_index":0,"text":"Do you mean a \"secondary agent\" in a multi-agent system (a helper/fallback agent), a secondary AI in a product, or something else? I can explain common roles and capabilities — here are typical things a secondary agent can do:\n\n- Monitoring & alerting: watch primary systems, detect anomalies, raise alerts or start remediation.\n- Fallback / redundancy: take over tasks if the primary agent fails or is unavailable.\n- Specialised subtasking: handle niche responsibilities (e.g., vision, speech, NLP, billing) while the primary handles orchestration.\n- Data collection & preprocessing: gather, clean, and normalize data for the primary agent or models.\n- Tool integration & execution: call external APIs, run scripts, or control devices on behalf of the system.\n- Validation & safety checks: verify outputs, filter unsafe content, enforce policies before results are released.\n- Human-in-the-loop escalation: surface uncertain cases to human operators and incorporate their feedback.\n- Logging, auditing & observability: record decisions, maintain audit trails, and provide explanations.\n- Simulation & planning support: run simulations, evaluate alternatives, or provide contingency plans.\n- Ensemble/consensus: compare multiple models/agents and pick or combine results for higher reliability.\n\nConstraints to consider:\n- Permissions & data access (what it’s allowed to see/do).\n- Latency and performance budgets.\n- Degree of autonomy vs. human control.\n- Security, privacy, and compliance requirements.\n- Failure modes and recovery procedures.\n\nTell me the context (product, system design, or specific agents you’re working with) and what you want the secondary agent to accomplish, and I’ll give concrete design options and example workflows.","logprobs":[]}

